  <div class="container">
    <h3>API Endpoints</h3>
  <div class="container">
    <h4>Power Conversion</h4>
    <p>The power conversion endpoint is a simple endpoint for converting small or large amounts of power quickly and easily. </p>
    <strong style="color:blue; font-size: 18px;">/power</strong>
    <div class="container">
      <br>
      <strong>Available parameters: </strong>
      <p>Units <strong>(required)</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>watts</li>
        <li>kilowatts</li>
        <li>megawatts</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <strong>Example Request: </strong><br>
      <div class="well well-sm">
        GET /power?<em>watts</em>=123456
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <strong>Response: </strong>
      <pre>
{
    "watts":123456,
    "kilowatts":123.456,
    "megawatts":0.123456,
    "status_code":200
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <h4>Energy Conversion</h4>
    <p>The energy conversion endpoint is used to convert power and time into energy.</p>
    <strong style="color:blue; font-size: 18px;">/energy</strong>
    <div class="container">
      <br>
        <strong>Available parameters:</strong>
          <p>Units <strong>(required)</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>watts</li>
              <li>kilowatts</li>
              <li>megawatts</li>
            </ul>
          <p>Time <strong>(required)</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>hours</li>
            <li>minutes <em>coming soon!</em></li>
            <li>seconds <em>coming soon!</em></li>
          </ul>
        <br>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
    <strong>Example Request: </strong><br>
    <div class="well well-sm">
      GET /energy?<em>watts</em>=123456&<em>hours</em>=1
    </div>
  </div>
    <div class="container">
    <strong>Response: </strong>
      <pre>
{
    "watt_hours":123456,
    "kilowatt_hours":123.456,
    "megawatt_hours":0.123456,
    "status_code":200
}</pre>
  </div>
  </div>
